# PR Branching Convention

Always create feature branches from the latest `main`, never from another feature branch.

```bash
# ✅ CORRECT
git fetch origin
git checkout -b my-feature origin/main

# ❌ WRONG — accidentally includes unmerged work from another branch
git checkout -b my-feature some-other-feature-branch
```

Before creating a PR, verify the branch contains only the intended commits:

```bash
git log --oneline origin/main..HEAD
```

If extra commits from another branch are present, create a fresh branch off `origin/main` and cherry-pick only the intended commits.
